♂. —Length 13 mm., length of antennae 5 mm. Head and eyes black with black pile. Eyes contiguous above and widely separated below the antennae. Antennae contiguous at base. ﬁrst joint scarcely visible and yellow, second joint small, black and ring-like. The third antenna] joint has a founded. short basal portion which expands into a very large surface, ﬂattened. very thin and rounded at the end. The third joint is about four times as long as the head and about 6- io as wide as long‘ it is velvety black and destitute of pile. Proboscis rudimentary, slender, cylindrical and pointed, covered with very short black pile. Face black. deeply excavated below the antennae (see Pl. XI,
fig . 1b
). Occiput slightly swollen, the cheeks shining black and pointed below the eyes. Ocellar tubercle rudimentary, black, with a central depression which is thinly black pilose; ocelli absent.
